03/22/2021,748.2307(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,01/14/2022,01/14/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,A child was placed in isolation with no contact allowed with other residents as a form of punishment. ,"An extension was granted due AR request. 

An inspection was conducted at the operation. A walk through of the area where the child was isolated was completed. There was a discussion with the Case Manager that all staff have been informed of proper searches of a child in care, upper management will conduct the search, there will be 2 staff present and there will be a male staff member available if a boy needs to be searched (because all upper management are female). All staff have been advised that they are not to seclude a child and should use other methods such as a search if the need arises or a heightened supervision of 1 on 1. "
