11/08/2020,748.685(c)(2) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,12/12/2020,12/08/2020,Individual Standards Evaluated,High,Yes,"A staff did not follow their policies regarding a youth returning a razor that is checked out during showers and required to check back into the staff after use. This allowed the youth to use the razor and inflicted self-harm.  
","Agency sent an e-mail stating: 
All razors provided to Residents must be signed in and out by both the resident and staff. All razors are single-use razors and are to be disposed of after single use by the resident.  Before staff issues a razor to a resident, the resident must initial the razor sign out log, with the date and time that the razor was signed outstaff will also initial that the razor was issued. 
The resident is required to return the razor with staff initialing the time of return and disposal of the razor.

The resident should be allowed ample time to use the razor for personal grooming and hygiene; however, if the staff deems that the resident has had more than ample time (over 45 mins), staff should retrieve the razor from the resident.
"
